        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 9:03AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 903 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Jonesboro, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Jonesboro, Chatham, Hodge, North Hodge, East Hodge, Quitman, Eros,
Caderville and Mineral Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
